---
title: "Displaying matlab contribution in Google Sites"
layout: default
---

<p>Many professors and students use google sites for their academic site. It might be required to display your mathworks profile in your google site. The older method to embed another webpage was to simply use the IFrame gadget from the Insert menu. Currently, the iframe elements do not work in the google sites as a security measure. So I was googling around to find a way to show my mathworks contribution in my google site. I couldn't find any.</p>
<div><font face="georgia, serif">Step 1: In the <a href="http://www.mathworks.in/matlabcentral/fileexchange/?term=authorid:319814">mathworks fileexchange page</a>, you'll see a subscribe button on the top right. Clicking on this gives an RSS feed of the files submitted to mathworks. Copy this RSS link.</font></div>
<div><font face="georgia, serif"><br>
</font></div>
<div><font face="georgia, serif">
<div style="display:block;text-align:center;margin-right:auto;margin-left:auto"><a href="https://sites.google.com/site/sreeprasannar/blog/howtodisplayyourmathworkscontributioningooglesites/screenshot.128.jpg?attredirects=0" imageanchor="1"><img alt="Mathworks RSS feed button" src="https://sites.google.com/site/sreeprasannar/blog/howtodisplayyourmathworkscontributioningooglesites/screenshot.128.jpg?height=242&amp;width=400" height="242" border="0" width="400"></a></div>
<br>
</font></div>
<div><font face="georgia, serif">Step 2: Create a new page or go to the page where you want to insert the mathworks file list. Go to the edit mode of the page and select 'More gadgets' from the insert menu.&nbsp;</font></div>
<div><font face="georgia, serif"><br>
</font></div>
<div><font face="georgia, serif">Step 3: Search for 'RSS'. There was only one gadget when I tried. Nevertheless, choose a gadget that can show a RSS feed. I use <a href="http://www.gstatic.com/sites-gadgets/rss-sites/rss_sites.xml">this garget.</a></font></div>
<div><font face="georgia, serif"><br>
</font></div>
<div><font face="georgia, serif">Step 4: Add the mathworks RSS link into the gadget properties dialog.</font></div>
<div><font face="georgia, serif"><br>
</font></div>
<div><font face="georgia, serif">You are done. This will show a list of files in the mathworks RSS. Interested visitors can click on a script to reach the official mathworks page where the script is stored.</font></div>
<div><font face="georgia, serif"><br>
</font></div>
<div><font face="georgia, serif">This is <a href="https://sites.google.com/site/sreeprasannar/mathworks">my mathworks page</a> with the RSS feed in this site.</font></div>
<div><font face="georgia, serif"><br>
</font></div>
